---
const personalProjects = [
  {
    title: "Squash Performance Analytics",
    description:
      "End-to-end analytics pipeline built with DuckDB, SQL and Python. Layered data models (staging, marts) feed a win probability prediction model based on historical performance, recent form, and match metrics. Makefile orchestration for a modular SQL + Python workflow.",
    tags: ["Python", "DuckDB", "SQL", "Data Modeling", "Makefile"],
    href: "https://github.com/wastaja/squash-performance-analytics",
  },
  {
    title: "Cheese Analytics Pipeline",
    description:
      "Data pipeline to collect and analyze product data using Python, SQL, and DuckDB. Web scraping with requests + BeautifulSoup extracts structured data from a real-world website. Includes data cleaning, standardization, feature engineering, and a similarity scoring model for product recommendations. Modular Python scripts + Makefile orchestration.",
    tags: ["Python", "DuckDB", "SQL", "Web Scraping", "BeautifulSoup"],
    href: "https://github.com/wastaja/cheese-analytics-pipeline",
  },
];
---

<section id="projects" class="px-6 py-28 md:px-10">
  <div class="reveal mx-auto max-w-6xl">
    <p
      class="font-body mb-3 text-sm font-medium tracking-[0.3em] uppercase"
      style="color: var(--color-accent);"
    >
      03 / Projects
    </p>
    <h2
      class="font-heading mb-14 text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight uppercase md:text-7xl"
      style="color: var(--color-text);"
    >
      Projects
    </h2>

    <!-- Personal Projects -->
    <h3
      class="font-heading mb-6 text-sm font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase"
      style="color: var(--color-muted);"
    >
      Personal Projects
    </h3>
    <div class="mb-20 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
      {
        personalProjects.map((project) => (
          <a
            href={project.href}
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="group flex h-full flex-col rounded-2xl border p-8 transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1"
            style="border-color: var(--color-border);"
          >
            <h3
              class="font-heading mb-4 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight uppercase"
              style="color: var(--color-text);"
            >
              {project.title}
            </h3>
            <p
              class="font-body mb-6 text-base leading-relaxed"
              style="color: var(--color-muted);"
            >
              {project.description}
            </p>
            <div class="mb-6 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
              {project.tags.map((tag) => (
                <span
                  class="font-body rounded-full border px-3 py-1 text-xs"
                  style="border-color: var(--color-border); color: var(--color-text);"
                >
                  {tag}
                </span>
              ))}
            </div>
            <span
              class="font-body mt-auto inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-semibold tracking-wide uppercase transition-opacity"
              style="color: var(--color-accent);"
            >
              View on GitHub
              <span class="transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-1">
                &rarr;
              </span>
            </span>
          </a>
        ))
      }
    </div>

    <!-- Work Projects -->
    <div id="work-projects">
      <h3
        class="font-heading mb-2 text-sm font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase"
        style="color: var(--color-muted);"
      >
        Work Projects
      </h3>
      <p
        class="font-body mb-8 text-sm"
        style="color: var(--color-muted);"
      >
        Internal tools built at Just Join IT. Code is private — descriptions cover architecture and approach.
      </p>

      <!-- Internal Analytics Dashboards -->
      <div class="mb-6 rounded-2xl border p-8" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">
        <div class="mb-5 flex items-baseline gap-3">
          <h3
            class="font-heading text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight uppercase"
            style="color: var(--color-text);"
          >
            Internal Analytics Dashboards
          </h3>
          <span class="font-body text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">Just Join IT, 2025–2026</span>
        </div>

        <p class="font-body mb-1 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide" style="color: var(--color-muted);">Context</p>
        <p class="font-body mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
          Sales and Customer Success teams were managing NLA client data in formula-heavy Google Sheets that broke at scale — slow, unsortable, no audit trail.
        </p>

        <p class="font-body mb-2 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide" style="color: var(--color-muted);">What I built</p>
        <p class="font-body mb-3 text-base" style="color: var(--color-muted);">Two production internal dashboards replacing the legacy workflow entirely.</p>
        <ul class="mb-4 space-y-2">
          <li class="font-body flex gap-3 text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text);">
            <span style="color: var(--color-accent); flex-shrink: 0;">—</span>
            <span>Designed full data architecture: Snowflake (dbt models, bronze/silver/gold) → Supabase (PostgreSQL + RLS + Auth) → Lovable (React frontend)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="font-body flex gap-3 text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text);">
            <span style="color: var(--color-accent); flex-shrink: 0;">—</span>
            <span>Automated daily Snowflake → Supabase sync via GitHub Actions (drop-recreate strategy with automatic schema drift propagation)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="font-body flex gap-3 text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text);">
            <span style="color: var(--color-accent); flex-shrink: 0;">—</span>
            <span>Implemented row-level security, audit logging, and allowlist-based RPC protection</span>
          </li>
          <li class="font-body flex gap-3 text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text);">
            <span style="color: var(--color-accent); flex-shrink: 0;">—</span>
            <span>Built virtualized UI handling ~26K rows with client-side sorting, multi-level filtering, and bulk edit with CSV import</span>
          </li>
          <li class="font-body flex gap-3 text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text);">
            <span style="color: var(--color-accent); flex-shrink: 0;">—</span>
            <span>Integrated webhook pipeline: Supabase → Make → Google Sheets for real-time audit trail</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p class="font-body mb-1 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide" style="color: var(--color-muted);">Outcome</p>
        <p class="font-body mb-5 text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
          Replaced manual spreadsheet workflows for two teams; priorities and changes fully auditable per user.
        </p>

        <div class="mb-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          {["Snowflake", "dbt", "Supabase", "PostgreSQL", "GitHub Actions", "Lovable", "Python", "Make"].map((tag) => (
            <span
              class="font-body rounded-full border px-3 py-1 text-xs"
              style="border-color: var(--color-border); color: var(--color-text);"
            >
              {tag}
            </span>
          ))}
        </div>
        <p class="font-body text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted); font-style: italic;">Code private — internal tooling</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Account Merger -->
      <div class="rounded-2xl border p-8" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">
        <div class="mb-5 flex items-baseline gap-3">
          <h3
            class="font-heading text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight uppercase"
            style="color: var(--color-text);"
          >
            Account Merger — Data Migration
          </h3>
          <span class="font-body text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">Just Join IT, 2025–2026</span>
        </div>

        <p class="font-body mb-1 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide" style="color: var(--color-muted);">Context</p>
        <p class="font-body mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
          JustJoin IT and RocketJobs.pl are two brands under one company — and the time came to merge them into a single recruiter experience. Both platforms had separate employer accounts, separate logins, separate data. Merging incorrectly would mean one employer seeing another's data — a serious legal and trust issue.
        </p>

        <p class="font-body mb-2 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide" style="color: var(--color-muted);">What I did</p>
        <ul class="mb-4 space-y-2">
          <li class="font-body flex gap-3 text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text);">
            <span style="color: var(--color-accent); flex-shrink: 0;">—</span>
            <span>Audited and deduplicated ~50K employer panels and 60K non-unique users → 24K panels, 40K unique users</span>
          </li>
          <li class="font-body flex gap-3 text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text);">
            <span style="color: var(--color-accent); flex-shrink: 0;">—</span>
            <span>Designed deduplication logic to identify true unique entities across two systems with different data models</span>
          </li>
          <li class="font-body flex gap-3 text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text);">
            <span style="color: var(--color-accent); flex-shrink: 0;">—</span>
            <span>Ensured zero data leakage between legally separate entities throughout the migration</span>
          </li>
          <li class="font-body flex gap-3 text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text);">
            <span style="color: var(--color-accent); flex-shrink: 0;">—</span>
            <span>Coordinated with CS and Sales teams for edge cases where data signals were ambiguous — delegating manual verification where data alone wasn't enough</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p class="font-body mb-1 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide" style="color: var(--color-muted);">Outcome</p>
        <p class="font-body mb-5 text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
          Clean, merged account structure with full data isolation — migration completed without incidents.
        </p>

        <div class="mb-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          {["SQL", "Snowflake", "dbt", "PostgreSQL", "Data Migration"].map((tag) => (
            <span
              class="font-body rounded-full border px-3 py-1 text-xs"
              style="border-color: var(--color-border); color: var(--color-text);"
            >
              {tag}
            </span>
          ))}
        </div>
        <p class="font-body text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted); font-style: italic;">Code private — production data migration</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
